'''Vasant Kanya Mahavidyalaya''' ([[Hindi]]: <U+0935><U+0938><U+0902><U+0924> <U+0915><U+0928><U+094D><U+092F><U+093E> <U+092E><U+0939><U+093E><U+0935><U+093F><U+0926><U+094D><U+092F><U+093E><U+0932><U+092F>) also known as <u>VKM</u> and as <u>Vasant Kanya Mahavidyalaya PG college</u> is a women collage in [[Varanasi]] ([[India]]), affiliated with [[Benaras Hindu University]]. It was established in 1954 by Dr. Rohit Mehta.<ref name=" VKM ">{{cite news|title=VKM|publisher=College website|accessdate=Mar 2015|url=http://vkm.org.in/}}</ref><ref name=" History ">{{cite news|title=History|publisher=College website|accessdate=Mar 2015|url=http://vkm.org.in/history.asp}}</ref><ref name="Enrollment">{{cite news|title=Enrollment|publisher=educationinfoindia.com|accessdate=Mar 2015|url=http://www.educationinfoindia.com/others/l_index%5Bvkmkv%5D.html}}</ref><ref name="Affiliation">{{cite news|title=Affiliation|publisher=[[Benaras Hindu University|BHU]]|accessdate=Mar 2015|url=http://www.bhu.ac.in/VSW/}}</ref>
==History==
Vasant Kanya Mahavidyalaya was founded by Dr. Rohit Mehta in 1954. Dr. Mehta was inspired by Dr. [[Annie Besant]] and went on to found this college for women education, with the motto ''Education as Service''. The college is run by [[Besant Education Fellowship]] and situated in the compound of the [[Theosophical Society]] at Kamachha, [[Bhelupura]], [[Varanasi]].<ref name=" History "/>
